# ops/ha/.gitignore — keep HA runtime writes out of git.
#
# `ops/ha/` is bind-mounted into HA's `/config` (see docker-compose.yml).
# HA writes auth storage, the SQLite database, logs, the install ID, and
# various caches into this directory at runtime. None of those should be
# tracked: some contain secrets (`.storage/auth`, `secrets.yaml`),
# others churn on every boot.
#
# The ROOT .gitignore has `!ops/ha/` as a carve-out from the global
# `ops/*` rule. That means files inside ops/ha/ are not blocked by the
# root rules; THIS file is what filters HA's runtime droppings back out.
#
# Acceptance check (Phase 2.5 plan):
#   `git status --porcelain ops/ha/` returns empty after a freshly booted
#   HA container reaches ready state. If new HA-written paths surface in
#   future versions, extend this list until empty status is achieved.

# === HA core runtime state ===
.storage/
.cloud/
.uuid

# === Databases (SQLite recorder) ===
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.db-journal
home-assistant_v2.db*

# === Logs ===
*.log
*.log.*
home-assistant.log*

# === Caches and downloaded resources ===
tts/
deps/
image/
www/
.cache/

# === Secrets & generated config the user is expected to manage manually ===
secrets.yaml
known_devices.yaml
ip_bans.yaml

# === Misc HA scratch ===
.HA_VERSION
.config/
custom_components/

# Keep this file itself tracked (paranoia in case of glob expansion).
!.gitignore
